On the top Of yon magnolia‚ the loud turkey's voice Is heralding the dawn 3 from tree to tree Extends the wakening watch—note‚ far and wide, Till the whole woodlands echo with the cry. Now breaks the morning; but as yet no foot Hath mark'd the dews, nor sound of man is heard. Then first Ocellopan beheld, where near, Beneath the shelter of a half-roof'd hut, A sleeping stranger lay. He pointed him To Tlalala. The Tyger look'd around 3 N one else was nigh. “ Shall I descend,'’ he said, “ And strike him? here is none to see the deed.
